AUTHOR: Chester Booker

To run VAMIX:
1) Make sure the Vamix.jar file is set as executable.
2) Either double-click on the Vamix.jar file or type "java -jar Vamix.jar"
   into the command-line while in the directory of the .jar file.

Note: Please make sure your computer has vlcj installed.



HOTKEYS: 

Alt + S = Select Media Chooser
Alt + D = Downloader
Alt + U = Add Subtitle Panel
Alt + E = Add Effects Panel
Alt + A = Edit Audio Panel
Alt + T = Edit Text Panel
Alt + V = Edit Video Panel
Alt + J = Adjust Speed Panel

Alt + [ANYTHING ELSE] = Home
(Easy way to remember these is to look at the underlined letters on the buttons)



Features of Vamix:

- Media chooser. Select either a video or audio file and play it.

- Media downloader. Download an open-souce media file from a URL.

- Media player. Play, Pause, Fastforward, Rewind, Fullscreen, Mute, Skip, Change
  Volume of a selected media file.

- Subtitle Adder: - Add Subtitles
		  - Remove Subtitles
		  - Edit a Subtitle file

- Effect Adder: - Vertical Flip
		- Horizontal Flip
		- Blur Effect
		- Add a Watermark

- Audio Editor: - Replace Audio
		- Overlay Audio
		- Strip Audio
		- Extract Audio

- Video Editor: - Add Fade-in
		- Add Fade-out
		- Extract a segments of a video

- Speed Adjuster: - Speed up the video/audio
		  - Slow down the video/audio

- Text Editor*: - Decide what text to be added
	        - Add to beginning/end scene
	        - Choose Duration
	        - Choose Font
	        - Choose Size
	        - Choose Colour
	        - Choose Position
	        - Decide whether to add a shadow

		* There is the option to pre-view the text for 3 seconds.
		* Or permanently add it to the video.
		** You may save the currently selected options state.
		** Or load the last save options state.
